All 3 tests pass. Here's the summary of the fix:

**Pattern:** Replace the `out` parameter with a return value assignment.

```csharp
// MSTest v3 (old)
Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>(obj, out var typed);

// MSTest v4 (new)
var typed = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>(obj);
```

The method now returns the casted value directly instead of using an `out` parameter. Same assertion behavior, cleaner syntax. I also updated your MSTest package from `3.8.0` → `4.1.0`.
